#ROOM
Vnum     13251
Name     &GThe Northern Jungle Path&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     The gloomy trees of Duskwood abruptly give way to the vibrant, suffocating
heat of the Stranglethorn Vale jungle. Massive ferns and towering ancient
trees form a thick canopy overhead. The air is filled with the shrieks
of exotic birds and the roars of deadly predators.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13252
Desc      The path leads to a large dwarven encampment.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13252
Name     &GNesingwary's Expedition&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A large clearing in the dense jungle. Several sturdy canvas tents have
been erected here, surrounded by the mounted heads of massive panthers,
raptors, and tigers. Hemet Nesingwary and his crew use this camp as a
base of operations for their grand safari.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13251
Desc      The path leading back toward Duskwood.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13253
Desc      The deep jungle to the south.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13251 1 13252
  Reset E 1 13251 10 16
Reset O 0 13265 2 13252
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13253
Name     &GPanther Hunting Grounds&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     The shadows are incredibly deep here. The trees are scarred with deep
claw marks. This area is the favored hunting ground of the stealthy
Shadowmaw Panthers. You feel eyes watching you from the canopy above.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13252
Desc      Nesingwary's camp.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    13254
Desc      A rocky clearing favored by raptors.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13255
Desc      A heavily guarded military compound.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13256 2 13253
Reset O 0 13254 2 13253
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13254
Name     &GThe Raptor Ridge&d~
Sector   hills~
Desc     The thick jungle breaks open into a rocky ridge. The ground is littered
with chewed bones and brightly colored, shed feathers. Vicious, highly
intelligent Stranglethorn Raptors hunt in packs across this ridge.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    13253
Desc      The panther hunting grounds.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13255 2 13254
Reset O 0 13255 3 13254
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13255
Name     &GKurzen's Compound - Gates&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     A massive wooden palisade blocks the path south. The rogue Colonel
Kurzen has fortified this area, turning his former Stormwind soldiers
into a brainwashed, highly lethal mercenary army. Mindslaves patrol
the perimeter with blank, terrifying stares.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13253
Desc      The jungle path.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13256
Desc      The interior of the compound.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    13257
Desc      A scarred, deforested path.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13262 2 13255
Reset O 0 13259 1 13255
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13256
Name     &GKurzen's Compound - Command Tent&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     The heart of the rogue military operation. Stolen Alliance supplies and
cruel voodoo totems fill the tent. Colonel Kurzen stands here, utterly
mad, barking orders to his enthralled troops.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13255
Desc      The gates of the compound.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13261 1 13256
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13257
Name     &GThe Crystal Mine Approach&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The jungle has been completely clear-cut here. Stumps and shattered
trunks litter the ground. The Venture Trading Company is rapidly and
carelessly stripping the land of its natural resources.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    13255
Desc      Kurzen's Compound.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    13258
Desc      The Venture Co. Crystal Mine.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13259
Desc      Ancient stone ruins loom to the south.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13258 2 13257
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13258
Name     &dThe Venture Co. Crystal Mine&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    dark indoors~
Desc     A deep, artificial cave dug into the side of a hill. Sparks fly as
Goblin Mechanics desperately try to keep their massive shredders running.
Glowing blue crystals line the walls, pulsing with raw magic.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    13257
Desc      The approach outside.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13258 1 13258
  Reset E 1 13256 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13259
Name     &GThe Ruins of Zul'Kunda&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     Massive, moss-covered stone ziggurats rise from the jungle floor. These
ancient troll ruins are fiercely defended by the Bloodscalp tribe. The
smell of blood and dark voodoo hangs heavily in the air.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13257
Desc      The deforested path.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13260
Desc      The top of the ziggurat.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    13261
Desc      A quiet clearing deep in the jungle.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13260 2 13259
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13260
Name     &GZul'Kunda - The High Altar&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You stand at the peak of the ancient ziggurat. The stone altar is stained
crimson. Bloodscalp Hunters and Mystics perform dark rituals here,
sacrificing their enemies to the loa spirits of the jungle.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13259
Desc      The base of the ruins.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13260 1 13260
  Reset E 1 13261 10 16
Reset O 0 13258 2 13260
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13261
Name     &GBangalash's Clearing&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The jungle is unnervingly quiet here. The birds have stopped singing,
and the insects are silent. The grass is trampled down. This is the lair
of King Bangalash, the most feared predator in all of Stranglethorn.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    13259
Desc      The Ruins of Zul'Kunda.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13262
Desc      The deepest part of the jungle.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13257 1 13261
  Reset E 1 13262 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13262
Name     &GThe Deep Jungle&d~
Sector   forest~
Desc     The foliage is incredibly dense, blocking almost all light. Thick,
thorny vines snare your boots. Panthers and raptors hunt freely here,
far from the relative safety of the northern camps.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13261
Desc      Bangalash's Clearing.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13263
Desc      The grand walls of the Arena.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13255 1 13262
Reset M 0 13256 1 13262
Reset O 0 13260 3 13262
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13263
Name     &GGurubashi Arena - Entrance&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You stand before the colossal, ruined gates of the Gurubashi Arena. Once
the crown jewel of the troll empire, it is now a lawless, free-for-all
bloodbath. Elite Gurubashi Berserkers guard the entrance.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13262
Desc      The Deep Jungle.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    13264
Desc      The floor of the Arena.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13265
Desc      The Ruins of Zul'Mamwe.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13263 2 13263
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13264
Name     &GGurubashi Arena - The Pit&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The massive, circular floor of the arena. Blood stains the ancient
stone. There are no rules here, and no allegiances. Anyone who steps
into the pit is fair game. Periodically, a chest of treasure is placed
in the center, sparking absolute chaos.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    13263
Desc      The Arena Entrance.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 13263 1 13264
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     13265
Name     &GThe Ruins of Zul'Mamwe&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     More sprawling troll ruins, these heavily occupied by the Skullsplitter
tribe. Voodoo wards hang from the trees, and the smell of dark magic
is potent.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    13263
Desc      The Gurubashi Arena.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    13266
Desc      The Wild Shore.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    13269
Desc      Mistvale Valley.
~
